synopses.synopsis: An elaborate format and a deep American fascination for the theater world are undoubtedly responsible for much of the early success of The First Nighter Program. The illusion was that anyone might be transported to 'the little theater off Times Square' to witness an 'opening night performance' of a fine romantic comedy. - On the Air: The Encyclopedia of Old-Time Radio by John Dunning
